  <h2 class="section-title">TV Girl</h2>
  <p>TV Girl is an American indie pop band from San Diego, California. Formed in 2010, the group consists of Brad Petering, Jason Wyman and Wyatt Harmon. They are known for incorporating eclectic samples into their songs, creating a nostalgic, lo‑fi sound that mixes classic pop melodies with hip‑hop production techniques.</p>
  <h3 class="subsection-title">Discography</h3>
  <p>The band has released several albums and EPs, including <em>French Exit</em>, <em>Who Really Cares</em> and <em>Grapes Upon the Vine</em>. Their lyrics often explore themes of relationships, nostalgia and city life.</p>
