  <h2 class="section-title">The Smiths</h2>
  <p>The Smiths were an English rock band formed in Manchester in 1982. The classic line‑up featured vocalist Morrissey, guitarist Johnny Marr, bassist Andy Rourke and drummer Mike Joyce. The Smiths are considered one of the most influential bands of the 1980s and a cornerstone of the British independent music scene.</p>
  <h3 class="subsection-title">Musical Style</h3>
  <p>The Smiths' music is characterised by Marr's jangly guitar work and Morrissey's lyrical and vocal style. Their songs often deal with themes of loneliness, social alienation and romantic melancholy.</p>
